      • filterFoundResolvers

        public void filterFoundResolvers​(java.util.List<ImportResolver> importResolvers,
                                 java.io.File file)
        Provides for a capability by which a set of resolvers can be trimmed by a found sorter implementation. This provides great power to the sorter to force itself to be used over a group of other resolvers. Plugin implementers should take great caution in using this only when it is guaranteed to be the correct behavior.
        Parameters:
        importResolvers - the list of import resolvers that to filter. The modification are made directly to the importResolvers list.
        file - the file that is being considered for the resolvers.
